answers.textarea_31444284: The data for this measure is collected by the primary 911 switch operated by CAPCOG.  We retrieve the data on a monthly basis via the switch's web-based reporting tool, compile the data in a spreadsheet, and eventually load it into the department data warehouse.
answers.list_31441558_choice: yes, and it's on the data portal

metadata.user_agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/54.0.2840.71 Safari/537.36

answers.list_31441558_choice: yes, and it's on the data portal
answers.list_31441411_other: Compliance is calculated by the AQUA system
answers.textarea_31444284: AQUA is the "Advanced Quality Assurance" system created by the vendor of the triage tool used by EMS in the Communications Center.  The system guides reviewers through audits of a random sample of 911 calls, and calculates the compliance score used in the performance measure.
answers.textfield_31440655: AQUA [a COTS system designed for review of 911 calls]

hidden.m_name: Percent reduction of EMS transport to hospitals of enrolled CHP Clients

metadata.user_agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/54.0.2840.71 Safari/537.36

answers.textarea_31444284: The Apricot client management system is used to identify CHP clients, and to determine the duration of their enrollment in the program.  Based on information from this system, data regarding client contacts with the 911 system before and after their enrollment in the program is downloaded from the EMS Data Warehouse, and changes in utilization are calculated using Microsoft Excel.  This is currently done on an as-needed basis.
answers.textfield_31440655: Two Systems: Apricot (client management system) and EMS Data Warehouse

answers.textarea_31444284: In our department, KPIs /= data that citizens are interested in.
